		<div id="comment_body_65098823"><p><div class="quote"><p>Gen Zers have garnered a poor reputation with employers. Hiring managers have labeled them as the most difficult generation to work with, according to a Resume Genius report.</p></div><p>I truly feel for the actual hardworking GenZ applicant who actually <i>needs and would respect</i> an offer for employment. Because at 34%, that is feeding a bias that is going to eventually be assumed to be <i>accurate enough</i> to affect most everyone of that generation.</p><p>Spoiled little ghost-shits better hope the recession doesn&rsquo;t keep growing.  You&rsquo;ll be the last to be hired, and your <i>need</i> for employment isn&rsquo;t any different than the rest of us.  Professional Victim, isn&rsquo;t a well-paid position anymore.  Thankfully.</p></div>
	</div>

